This paper deals with the design and simulation of wireless communication systems, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networked Systems (cs.NI). The focus is on millimeter-wave frequencies, which is a subfield of Microwave and RF Engineering (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of directional antennas, which is relevant to System and Control (cs.SY) and Radio Frequency (cs.RF) subcategories.
